    "description": "The strategy is a single asset long only mean reversion overlay on US large cap equities, using a 14 period stochastic oscillator on SPY to identify short term oversold conditions and monetize the subsequent rebound. It targets environments where intraday pullbacks tend to revert, seeking to capture the typical bounce after momentum becomes temporarily stretched to the downside.\n\nThe system evaluates signals on hourly bars and enters a 100 percent notional long SPY position when the stochastic o",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a single asset long only mean reversion overlay on US large cap equities, using a 14 period stochastic oscillator on SPY to identify short term oversold conditions and monetize the subsequent rebound. It targets environments where intraday pullbacks tend to revert, seeking to capture the typical bounce after momentum becomes temporarily stretched to the downside.\n\nThe system evaluates signals on hourly bars and enters a 100 percent notional long SPY position when the stochastic oscillator falls below 30, indicating an oversold regime. It exits solely via a fixed take profit, liquidating the entire position once SPY reaches at least 5 percent above the position average entry price; there is no explicit stop loss, time based exit, or volatility scaling, so downside is managed only by the signal itself and full investment constraint. Data inputs are SPY hourly price bars used to compute the stochastic oscillator, with decisions made each bar after indicator warm up. The intended edge is short horizon mean reversion in a highly liquid benchmark ETF.",
